"Chaos in the Morning"  They have several people on staff all seemingly working and doing tasks, but it does not flow cohesively.  I think there should be a person on staff ensuring that the needs of the customers are met.  They need a leader to help expedite orders.  I order "On the Go" using the Dunkin app all the time.  This is so that by the time I reach Dunkin Donuts in 11 minutes, they will have my Egg and Cheese Wake Up Wrap and my small ice coffee with Almond milk and caramel swirl ready by the time I get there.  Simple right?  Well,  sure they get order, but there is no record of the order to be found on the Ready Table (the table that has all the orders waiting to be picked up).  When "On the Go" first started, they would get these pink receipts, and lay the receipts down, with the orders on top of them.  Now, they just put the food out, without the receipt, so you can't show the person at Dunkin that your order is incomplete, without taking out your phone, and showing it that way.  But they are so busy, that they can't stop to think about doing anything outside of their normal routine.  If the receipt was in full view, someone could ensure that the order is complete, before moving on to another.   However, what they do is, if your order is incomplete, they keep moving on to the next order regardless, and your order is left undone.  I've had to leave multiple times with incomplete orders because of it.  Another reason why I'm rating this place so low is because they would always have a long line of people waiting to order, and a backlog of people waiting for their order to be fulfilled.  Things like a small unsweetened ice tea, should not take 10 minutes to fulfill.  The Expediter should be there to give one off's like this, when items take less than 30 seconds to make.  It is for these reasons I give this Dunkin a two star rating.
